translations:
‘abends
			um sieben Uhr verliessen wir das Kloster und gingen zu Fuss bis zu
			dem Dorfe Qartmin’;

‘He
			took the needle, stuck it into his finger, and the black blood
			came out right away’ JL 20.7.44;

‘They brought me to the village. They (the military forces, f.)
			have taken out their (the villagers’) beds and demolished their
			walls’ LB 329;

‘When it (milk m.) had become a little bit hot, we put the
			ferment into it (pot f.), and it (?) became fine clabber, and we
			took it out with spoons’ JL 12.14.4;
